# n8n Workflow Credentials (example — safe to commit)
#
# Setup:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   Fill values in .env locally. Never commit .env.
#
# The agent appends new credential blocks when building workflows.
# After filling values, tell the agent to create credentials and continue.

# --- n8n instance (configured in .cursor/mcp.json, listed here for reference) ---
# Copy .cursor/mcp.json.example → .cursor/mcp.json and set these there:
# N8N_API_URL=
# N8N_API_KEY=

# --- Gmail OAuth ---
# Gmail credentials are usually wired in the n8n UI (OAuth), not in .env.
# Only add vars here if a workflow needs non-OAuth Gmail/ Google API secrets.

# Credential: Snowflake - Vitaquest 3PL
# Type: snowflake
# Workflows: 3PL - n8n builder
# Fields: account, username, password, warehouse, database, schema
SNOWFLAKE_VITAQUEST_ACCOUNT=
SNOWFLAKE_VITAQUEST_USERNAME=
SNOWFLAKE_VITAQUEST_PASSWORD=
SNOWFLAKE_VITAQUEST_WAREHOUSE=
SNOWFLAKE_VITAQUEST_DATABASE=
SNOWFLAKE_VITAQUEST_SCHEMA=

